.TH "lockdep_hardirqs_on_prepare" 9 "lockdep_hardirqs_on_prepare" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lockdep_hardirqs_on_prepare \- Prepare for enabling interrupts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" lockdep_hardirqs_on_prepare
.BI "(unsigned long ip "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ip" 12
Caller address
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Invoked before a possible transition to RCU idle from exit to user or
guest mode. This ensures that all RCU operations are done before RCU
stops watching. After the RCU transition \fBlockdep_hardirqs_on\fP has to be
invoked to set the final state.
